Root Cause — 3 Specific Problems Found
Problem 1: manifest.json and sw.js not uploaded yet
Your original index.html has <link rel="manifest" href="manifest.json"> — but these files don't exist in your repo yet. Have you actually uploaded manifest.json and sw.js to GitHub?

Problem 2: Icon files missing = PWA install blocked
Browsers refuse to show "Add to Home Screen" if the icons declared in manifest.json don't exist. No icon-192.png or icon-512.png = PWA won't install. This is the most common silent failure.

Problem 3: Brave specifically blocks PWA prompts by default
Brave has a known behaviour — it suppresses the install banner even when PWA criteria are met. You have to manually trigger it.

Fix — Do These Steps in Order
Step 1: Confirm files exist in your GitHub repo Go to github.com/37md/QuickCommerce — you should see these files listed:

index.html  ✓ (already there)
manifest.json  ← must add
sw.js          ← must add
icon-192.png   ← must add
icon-512.png   ← must add
Step 2: Create icons quickly (no design needed) Go to → https://favicon.io/favicon-generator/

Type "QC", pick any color, download
It gives you a zip with android-chrome-192x192.png and android-chrome-512x512.png
Rename them to icon-192.png and icon-512.png
Upload both to your GitHub repo
Step 3: Install on Brave specifically Brave hides the automatic banner. Do this manually:

Open https://37md.github.io/QuickCommerce/ in Brave
Tap the 3-dot menu (⋮) top right
Look for "Add to Home Screen" or "Install App"
If not visible → tap the address bar → look for a small install icon (⊕) on the right side
